���skip_xcvrdu��#!/usr/bin/env bash

declare -r EXIT_SUCCESS="0"

mkdir -p /var/sonic
echo "# Config files managed by sonic-config-engine" > /var/sonic/config_status

rm -f /var/run/rsyslogd.pid

supervisorctl start rsyslogd

# If this platform has synchronization script, run it
if [ -e /usr/share/sonic/platform/platform_wait ]; then
    /usr/share/sonic/platform/platform_wait
    EXIT_CODE="$?"
    if [ "${EXIT_CODE}" != "${EXIT_SUCCESS}" ]; then
        supervisorctl shutdown
        exit "${EXIT_CODE}"
    fi
fi

# If this platform has an lm-sensors config file, copy it to it's proper place
# and start lm-sensors
if [ -e /usr/share/sonic/platform/sensors.conf ]; then
    mkdir -p /etc/sensors.d
    /bin/cp -f /usr/share/sonic/platform/sensors.conf /etc/sensors.d/
    supervisorctl start lm-sensors
fi

# If this platform has a fancontrol config file, copy it to it's proper place
# and start fancontrol
if [ -e /usr/share/sonic/platform/fancontrol ]; then
    # Remove stale pid file if it exists
    rm -f /var/run/fancontrol.pid

    /bin/cp -f /usr/share/sonic/platform/fancontrol /etc/
    supervisorctl start fancontrol
fi


# If the sonic-platform package is not installed, try to install it
pip show sonic-platform > /dev/null 2>&1
if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
    SONIC_PLATFORM_WHEEL="/usr/share/sonic/platform/sonic_platform-1.0-py2-none-any.whl"
    echo "sonic-platform package not installed, attempting to install..."
    if [ -e ${SONIC_PLATFORM_WHEEL} ]; then
       pip install ${SONIC_PLATFORM_WHEEL}
       if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
          echo "Successfully installed ${SONIC_PLATFORM_WHEEL}"
       else
          echo "Error: Failed to install ${SONIC_PLATFORM_WHEEL}"
       fi
    else
       echo "Error: Unable to locate ${SONIC_PLATFORM_WHEEL}"
    fi
fi

# Managed by Ansible

#
#  /etc/rsyslog.conf    Configuration file for rsyslog.
#
#                       For more information see
#                       /usr/share/doc/rsyslog-doc/html/rsyslog_conf.html


#################
#### MODULES ####
#################

$ModLoad imuxsock # provides support for local system logging
$ModLoad imklog   # provides kernel logging support
#$ModLoad immark  # provides --MARK-- message capability

# provides UDP syslog reception
$ModLoad imudp
$UDPServerAddress 127.0.0.1 # bind to localhost before udp server run
$UDPServerRun 514

# provides TCP syslog reception
#$ModLoad imtcp
#$InputTCPServerRun 514


###########################
#### GLOBAL DIRECTIVES ####
###########################
#
# Use traditional timestamp format.
# To enable high precision timestamps, comment out the following line.
#
#$ActionFileDefaultTemplate RSYSLOG_TraditionalFileFormat

# Define a custom template
$template SONiCFileFormat,"%timegenerated:1:3:date-rfc3164% %timegenerated:9:10:date-rfc3339% %timegenerated:12:19:date-rfc3339%.%timegenerated:::date-subseconds% %timegenerated:::date-year% %HOSTNAME% %syslogseverity-text:::uppercase% %syslogtag%%!msg1:::sp-if-no-1st-sp%%!msg1:::drop-last-lf%\n"
$ActionFileDefaultTemplate SONiCFileFormat

# SONiCForwardingFormat is a RFC5424 compliant template for message forwarding.
# Ideally forwarding template should have used 'timestamp' property to preserve the original timestamp.
# But we used 'timegenerated' to keep timestamps in local log file and remote messages the same.
# Will have to revisit if there are use cases for deploying SONiC as message relay.
$template SONiCForwardingFormat,"<%pri%>1 %timegenerated:::date-rfc3339% %hostname% %app-name% %procid% %msgid% %structured-data% %!msg1%"

# Define broadcast message template (for use with :omusrmsg:)
$template SONiCWallMsgFormat,"\r\nMessage from syslogd@%HOSTNAME% at %timegenerated% ...\r\n %syslogtag% %!msg1%\n\r"

# Use a mutable message string for template output
set $!msg1 = $msg;

���pfx_filtert���ipv4u)	��#!/usr/bin/env bash

CONFIG_DB_IDX="4"
STATE_DB_IDX="6"
APP_DB_IDX='0'

is_ready=0

function wait_until_iface_ready
{
    IFACE_NAME=$1
    IFACE_CIDR=$2
    iter=20

    echo "Waiting until interface ${IFACE_NAME} is ready..."

    # Wait for the interface to come up
    # (i.e., interface is present in STATE_DB and state is "ok")
    while ((iter-- > 0)); do
        RESULT=$(sonic-db-cli STATE_DB HGET "INTERFACE_TABLE|${IFACE_NAME}|${IFACE_CIDR}" "state" 2> /dev/null)
        if [ x"$RESULT" == x"ok" ]; then
            echo "Interface ${IFACE_NAME} is ready!"
            is_ready=1
            break
        fi

        sleep 1
    done
}

function check_config_and_wait_until_iface_ready
{
    iter=20
    IFACE_NAME=$1
    IFACE_CIDR=$2
    IFACE_TYPE=$3

    # Checking for the changes in the config DB
    while ((iter-- > 0)); do
        RESULT=$(sonic-db-cli CONFIG_DB HGET "${IFACE_TYPE}|${IFACE_NAME}|${IFACE_CIDR}" "NULL" 2> /dev/null)
        if [ x"$RESULT" == x"NULL" ]; then
            wait_until_iface_ready ${IFACE_NAME} ${IFACE_CIDR}
            if [ "$is_ready" == 1 ]; then
                is_ready=0
                break
            fi
        else
            echo "Address configuration removed on the interface ${IFACE_NAME}"
            break
        fi

    done
}

function wait_until_vrf_ready
{
    secs=20
    VRF_NAME=$1

    if [ x"${VRF_NAME}" != x"default" ]; then
       echo "Waiting until VRF ${VRF_NAME} is ready..."

       # Wait for the VRF to come up
       # (i.e., VRF is present in STATE_DB and state is "ok")
       while ((secs-- > 0)); do
           RESULT=$(sonic-db-cli STATE_DB HGET "VRF_TABLE|${VRF_NAME}" "state" 2> /dev/null)
           if [ x"$RESULT" == x"ok" ]; then
               echo "VRF ${VRF_NAME} is ready!"
               break
           fi

           sleep 1
       done
    fi
}

function wait_until_sag_iface_ready
{
    secs=20
    VLAN_NAME=$1
    SAG_GWIP=$2

    echo "Waiting until SAG interface on ${VLAN_NAME} is ready..."

    while ((secs-- > 0)); do
        RESULT=$(sonic-db-cli APPL_DB HGET "VRRP_TABLE:${VLAN_NAME}|${SAG_GWIP}" "sag" 2> /dev/null)
        if [ x"$RESULT" == x"yes" ]; then
            echo "SAG interface on ${VLAN_NAME} is ready!"
               break
           fi

        sleep 1
    done
}
